## Historical Notes

### Completed prior task: opencode runtime hooks skill improvement
- Analyzed debug JSONL files with and without event hook enabled.
- Documented the distinction between hooks and events: hooks are top-level interception points and can mutate outputs; events are read-only runtime notifications nested under `type: "event"` when the event hook is enabled.
- Updated `skills/opencode-runtime-hooks/` documentation, including comprehensive hook/event payload references and runtime sequence notes.
